## Language

ALL content MUST be in English. This includes SKILL.md files, config.yaml, ai-context/ files, openspec/ artifacts, and commit messages. No exceptions.

## Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Skill directories | kebab-case | `project-audit/`, `sdd-propose/` |
| Skill entry point | UPPER | `SKILL.md` |
| SDD phase skills | `sdd-[phase]` prefix | `sdd-propose`, `sdd-apply` |
| Meta-tool skills | `project-[action]` prefix | `project-audit`, `project-fix` |
| Tech skills | `[tech]-[version]` | `react-19`, `nextjs-15` |
| SDD change names | kebab-case descriptive | `improve-project-audit` |
| Archived changes | `YYYY-MM-DD-[name]` | `2026-02-23-add-project-fix` |

## SKILL.md Structure

Every SKILL.md must declare a `format:` field in YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
name: skill-name
description: >
  One-line description.
format: procedural   # valid values: procedural | reference | anti-pattern
---
```

Format-to-section mapping:

| `format:` value | Required main section |
|-----------------|----------------------|
| `procedural` (default) | `## Process` |
| `reference` | `## Patterns` or `## Examples` |
| `anti-pattern` | `## Anti-patterns` |

All formats require `**Triggers**` and `## Rules`.

## Git Conventions

- Commit messages in English
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `docs:`, `chore:`
- Config changes: edit in repo → `bash install.sh` → `git commit`
- Memory capture: `bash sync.sh` → `git add memory/` → `git commit`
- Commit after each SDD phase (at minimum after apply and after archive)

## Error Handling

- Bash: `set -e` + `|| true` for expected-failures
- SKILL.md: guard clauses with explicit "Stop here if…" statements
- Sub-agent return codes: `status: ok|warning|blocked|failed`
- Error handling at system boundaries only (user input, external APIs)

## Working Principles

- Clean and readable code over "clever" code
- No over-engineering: only what is necessary for the current task
- No obvious comments; only where the logic is not self-evident
- No speculative features or unnecessary backwards-compatibility hacks
- Tests as first-class citizens

## PRD Convention

A Product Requirements Document (PRD) is optional and precedes the SDD cycle for user-facing or product-level changes. Template: `docs/templates/prd-template.md`.

## ADR Convention

Architectural Decision Records use Nygard format. Location: `docs/adr/NNN-short-title.md`. Template: `docs/templates/adr-template.md`. The index `docs/adr/README.md` must be kept updated with every ADR (number, title, status). Valid statuses: Proposed, Accepted, Deprecated, Superseded.
